WEBVTT

00:00:02.129 --> 00:00:04.530
Philippians chapter 2 and verse 3,

00:00:04.530 --> 00:00:08.830
with humility, consider others superior to you.

00:00:08.830 --> 00:00:11.269
These words penned by the Apostle Paul

00:00:11.269 --> 00:00:15.470
really reflect a message that Jesus tried again and again

00:00:15.470 --> 00:00:18.070
to get across to his apostles.

00:00:18.070 --> 00:00:20.989
In fact, let's look at one account in Mark chapter 10,

00:00:20.989 --> 00:00:25.699
verse 42 and 43.

00:00:25.699 --> 00:00:29.199
Mark chapter 10, verses 42.

00:00:29.199 --> 00:00:33.100
It says, but Jesus called them to him and said to them,

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:36.100
you know that those who appear to be ruling the nations

00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:38.539
lorded over them, and their great ones

00:00:38.539 --> 00:00:41.060
wheeled authority over them.

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:44.020
This must not be the way among you,

00:00:44.020 --> 00:00:46.460
but whoever wants to be great among you

00:00:46.460 --> 00:00:48.820
must be your minister.

00:00:48.820 --> 00:00:52.939
And with humility, consider others superior to you.

00:00:52.939 --> 00:00:55.020
Now, why was Jesus so concerned

00:00:55.020 --> 00:00:59.020
that his disciples learned this lesson of humility?

00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:03.820
Because Jesus knew that lack of humility is contrary

00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:05.260
to Jehovah's personality.

00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:07.620
If we don't have humility, Jehovah's Holy Spirit

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:08.659
cannot flow.

00:01:08.659 --> 00:01:11.939
Psalm 138, in verse 1, says that Jehovah only knows

00:01:11.939 --> 00:01:13.859
the haughty from a distance.

00:01:14.819 --> 00:01:18.140
But Jesus also knew that lack of humility

00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:21.180
disrupts the peace of God's people.

00:01:21.180 --> 00:01:24.739
And without peace, Jehovah's Spirit cannot flow either.

00:01:24.739 --> 00:01:27.180
We may think of first Corinthians 14 and 33.

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:31.140
This is Jehovah is a God of peace.

00:01:31.140 --> 00:01:33.099
Now, it's adventurous as we look at the accounts

00:01:33.099 --> 00:01:36.540
that Jesus recognized that when his disciples

00:01:36.540 --> 00:01:39.099
lost their peace, when they were arguing,

00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:41.900
when they were bickering among themselves,

00:01:41.900 --> 00:01:44.379
it was because they were not applying the principle

00:01:44.379 --> 00:01:46.140
in today's text.

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:47.219
Let's look at another account.

00:01:47.219 --> 00:01:50.379
If you look back a page to Mark chapter nine

00:01:50.379 --> 00:01:57.500
in verse 33, it says, and they came into cavernium.

00:01:57.540 --> 00:01:59.180
Now, when he was inside the house,

00:01:59.180 --> 00:02:01.260
he put the questions to them,

00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:03.980
what were you arguing about on the road?

00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:05.739
What were you arguing about?

00:02:05.739 --> 00:02:07.620
Well, you look at verse 35, they were quiet

00:02:07.620 --> 00:02:11.099
because they were arguing about who was greater.

00:02:11.099 --> 00:02:12.259
Now, you think about this.

00:02:12.259 --> 00:02:14.539
These were grown men.

00:02:14.539 --> 00:02:16.620
Do you really think they were walking down the road

00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:17.780
saying, well, I'm greater than you are?

00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:21.460
No, I'm the greatest there is, maybe, but maybe not.

00:02:21.460 --> 00:02:24.259
These were grown mature men.

00:02:24.259 --> 00:02:26.979
But Jesus, in his wisdom of human nature,

00:02:26.979 --> 00:02:30.539
being able to read hearts knew what they were arguing

00:02:30.539 --> 00:02:33.099
about, the root of it, the topic didn't matter.

00:02:33.099 --> 00:02:37.139
The real issue was that it was a lack of humility.

00:02:37.139 --> 00:02:39.979
And notice what he says in verse 35.

00:02:39.979 --> 00:02:43.300
It says, so we said, now call the 12 and said to them,

00:02:43.300 --> 00:02:45.460
if anyone wants to be first,

00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:49.580
he must be last of all and minister of all.

00:02:49.580 --> 00:02:50.780
Have humility.

00:02:50.780 --> 00:02:54.259
Consider others superior to you.

00:02:54.259 --> 00:02:58.539
At Luke 9, verse 46 and 47, when there was a dispute,

00:02:58.539 --> 00:03:01.219
that account says, Jesus, knowing the reasoning

00:03:01.219 --> 00:03:04.860
of their hearts, counseled them on humility.

00:03:04.860 --> 00:03:07.860
He saw right through the argument, right through the issue,

00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:10.979
and isolated the real problem, lack of humility.

00:03:11.939 --> 00:03:13.539
Now, when you think about it, isn't it true

00:03:13.539 --> 00:03:17.539
that that's usually what is behind petty arguments,

00:03:17.539 --> 00:03:20.500
disputes, disagreements we may have?

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:23.379
See, if Jesus was among us, would he say,

00:03:24.060 --> 00:03:26.460
what were you arguing about in the office?

00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:29.020
What were you arguing about in the room?

00:03:29.020 --> 00:03:31.379
See, whether it's between marriage mates,

00:03:31.379 --> 00:03:33.460
those of us working together here at Bethel,

00:03:33.460 --> 00:03:36.699
bodies of elders, publishers in the congregation,

00:03:36.699 --> 00:03:39.219
what's the lesson for us?

00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:41.259
Well, the lesson is that when there seems

00:03:41.259 --> 00:03:45.020
to be a lack of peace, when there seems to be tension

00:03:45.020 --> 00:03:49.580
or arguing, the first person we should look at is ourselves.

00:03:49.620 --> 00:03:53.620
Am I really arguing over who is greater?

00:03:53.620 --> 00:03:54.979
Now, an account that always comes to mind

00:03:54.979 --> 00:03:57.300
when I think about this is that of Hagar,

00:03:57.300 --> 00:03:58.900
Sarah's Egyptian made servant.

00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:01.500
If you turn back to Genesis chapter 16

00:04:02.900 --> 00:04:04.659
and we're familiar with this account, Sarah,

00:04:04.659 --> 00:04:08.219
or Sarah at the time, was not able to become pregnant,

00:04:08.219 --> 00:04:11.860
Hagar became pregnant, and as soon as Hagar became pregnant,

00:04:11.860 --> 00:04:13.699
peace went out of the family, there was tension,

00:04:13.699 --> 00:04:15.340
there was bickering, there was arguing,

00:04:15.340 --> 00:04:17.819
things escalated to the point of Sarah

00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:21.459
humiliating Hagar and chasing her away into the wilderness.

00:04:21.459 --> 00:04:23.819
Now, we may first read this and go, poor Hagar,

00:04:23.819 --> 00:04:26.459
this young pregnant girl, Sarah is just jealous,

00:04:26.459 --> 00:04:30.740
Sarah is got the problem, was at the case.

00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:32.259
Well, we don't have all the facts of the matter,

00:04:32.259 --> 00:04:35.019
